  "design_notes": {
    "vbn_generation": "Direct rename of internal nbias node. Ground-referred by M1 diode connection.",
    "vbcn_generation": "NMOS diode (W=0.84 L=20) to ground. Current from PMOS mirror (XM8 W=4 L=4). Vgs sets vbcn directly, no body effect.",
    "vbp_generation": "Resistor (xhigh_po W=0.35 L=300, ~2.2 MΩ) from VDD to vbp + NMOS current sink (W=1.7 L=4, gate=vbn). Resistor positive TC partially cancels NMOS current TC for improved temperature stability (±38mV vs ±145mV with PMOS diode approach).",
    "vbcp_generation": "Resistor (xhigh_po W=0.35 L=650) from vbp to vbcp. NMOS current sink (W=0.84 L=16, gate=vbn). VDD-tracking because vbp tracks VDD.",
    "ss_corner_workaround": "W=0.84 used for all new PMOS/NMOS to avoid SKY130 ss-corner BSIM4 model bin .41 Pclm<0 issue with W=0.42."
